caption: One of the first places I visited when I moved to Chicago, and still one of my top go-tos. Perfect date/cozy atmosphere, especially when it's cold out!
american food and service at this spot is very good. Normally I would have posted a pic but food looked so good I couldn't stop. Prices are decent.
The service is consistently prompt, excellent mood, nice staff. Will eat here again when I am nearby.
Awesome place to get drinks for a date or with friends. Lighting seemed a little too high but overall great experience.

ordered a medium rare burger for delivery and it was well done, placed other orders and my coworkers orders where also incorrect,  for the price you pay for their burgers you would expect to be better than making this small mistakes

The cutest brunch spot that's perfect for a date or for groups! Very picture-worthy decor and great tasting food. Knocked off one star since there was nothing spectacular about the menu and service was slow at times.
I had the cheese curds and the seated ahi tuna. Both were really good, although there could have been more tuna on that plate.
Great service,  the food was under whelming
Awesome burger and the oysters were sooo fresh!
Cool spot

The pasta was drenched in mushrooms. The couple next to our table who was on their first date got a 10 minute warning to leave because other guests were waiting. A situation like that could have been handled much better than giving a couple out for their first date a 10 minute warning to leave. Seating is very cramped. The only thing good was the drink we ordered but there are endless options for drinks in Chicago.

Great spot, very accommodating and friendly staff, including back of house.  We came to get oysters (not on the late night menu) and they readily adapted and served us some in minutes.  Excellent short rib french dip sandwich!  Some good, creative cocktails as well.  Location is so chill and the gf and I both love it. Check it out!
One of the best whiskey bars in Chicago.
Food is really good, they have some nice higher end appetizers. The atmosphere is classy but comfortable. And the staff is great. Perfect 2nd+ date spot.
Love the happy hour but getting a table without a reservation is going to. be a struggle. Hover around the bar until someone leaves or come really early
Amazing whiskey tasting, great food and passionate staff.  Sorry we almost accidentally stiffed our host!!!
Good spot for a date.  I'd rate it 5 stars if it weren't for the bartender seeming impatient for us taking our time looking at the menu before ordering a drink.
Fantastic service. Great beverage program.
My favorite place in Chicago. Great food, great drinks, great ambiance, and the best lunch specials.

Ok. Let me start by saying, EXCELLENT customer service. Our waiter, Anthony, was so informative, friendly, and just an absolute perfect addition to the experience. I came here for my birthday (never heard of the place) and was not disappointed. The cocktails were excellent, the balance of bitterness to the small amount of citrus and sweet in the old fashioned was delightful. Ordered the salmon and the steak frites, along with other appetizers, and everything was cooked to perfection. Will be back again. If you’re looking for a great atmosphere, that’s low key, and also warm and inviting. This is the spot.

Fantastic food, trendy vibe, and fantastic service. I highly recommend the old fashioned, the oysters, the steak frites, and the bourbon milkshake. Anthony was a fantastic server with great recommendations throughout our time there. We will definitely be back soon!
Cool vibe, great food, and great service. I'm not a whiskey fan, but the whiskey selection is extensive. I recommend happy hour (5-6:30) for great deals on cocktails.

Been 3 times. Twice the steaks were among the best I've ever had. Went on a Sunday recently though and it was just OK. Which is not great considering the cost.  If you go on a weeknight expect it to be busy.  Staff is friendly and knowledgeable.

Absolutely fabulous experience.  First off, my fiancee and I loved the decor, the look reminded me of if a Supper Club was crossed with a Speakeasy.  We got there for Happy Hour to get the $1.50 oysters (they were quite delicious, but I don't recall the variety, medium sized with slight brine).  After some oysters we just kind of shared our way through the Small Fare section and thoroughly enjoyed the mussels (the sauce they used was crazy good) as well as the crispy rock shrimp.  As for the drinks, we started with some cocktails (the FR old fashioned was one of the best I've had) and then asked our server for whiskey recs because their whiskey list is EXTENSIVE.  Anthony (who was our server) was the BEST.  We told him which whiskeys we've tried and enjoyed and he put together tasting flights for us that stretched our palates but were right on point as well.  Would 100% recommend this place and for the best experience make sure you come when you have time to sit down and enjoy it all.
One of my favorite spots in the city for sure!
The best meal I’ve had in a long time. Got the bourbon burger. The drinks I had were phenomenal as as well. Highly recommend the, “bourbon boy”. Our waitress was very knowledgeable and kind as well.
Would definitely go again. Great selections and food with excellent service.

This was my first time here and My waiter Anthony made my experience great. My boyfriend and I had a great experience. He made sure I enjoyed my meals and drinks! He went above and beyond!!! I will be back because of his great service!!!
The food is awesome. High quality prep and ingredients for a price that's a deal for the location and what you get.
Happy hour deals, wine specials on Monday, great service and warm atmosphere. 10/10 will for sure be going back.
Really good drinks, priced as bouergois-y as possible. Also, it's going to be crowded. Really crowded.
Loved the food, drinks, and atmosphere. A little loud though

I've only come here during the lunch hours, but they have an excellent deal that runs from 11:30am to 2pm that deserves 5 stars on its own.  For a minimum purchase of what I believe is $12, certain wines & beers are $1 each (minimum 2 drinks ya sauce-heads) and then there's some equally cheap martini & cocktail offers.  Great overall ambiance. Not sure what the place is like during the evening hours, but if you want a half sandwich, side salad with a little yum-yum juice on the side - you can't go wrong with The Franklin Room!

Best meal I've had in a few months. Andrew was a great waiter. He gave a good suggestion on wine and let us know about the specials for the evening. My girlfriend and I were impressed with every but of our experience. Great ambience, great food, excellent service. We will definitely back.
Wonderful and deep scotch and whisky list to pair with the second best burger in town (Owen & Engine still remains at the top spot) or the rich and delcious cuts of steak they serve.
Great steak, and the environment was nice.
One of the best bourbon collections in Chicago

Lunch + drink special is beyond fantastic. High quality booze and food all around. Great for a Friday lunch. Only downside is that I've gotten some pretty sub par fish here, but the staff was insanely accommodating, so I even feel bad knocking it a star.

Anyone who rates this place less than 5 stars has lost their mind.  Everything about this place was fantastic.  Food, drinks, service, atmosphere and aesthetics were all exceptional.  Highly recommend!

Excellent selection of whiskeys, very short list of wines, limited choice of beef entrees. Steak Frites is sliced hanger steak so I passed on that. Waygu Sirloin was very, very tough (no steak knives btw) and over cooked; gray throughout which is not medium rare. No grill marks on the meat. I'm pretty sure they use a microwave and therefore the toughness and gray all over color/texture. I would have told our waiter but we only saw him three times. Would have ordered a second whiskey and then later a second glass of wine if the first hadn't arrived until I was almost done but, you know, no waiter. Also, 4oz pour of wine in a big glass looks cheap and the vegetables were cold - I could go on but you get the idea. Come on, Union Hospitality Group, at least pretend like you care or is it the GM at this restaurant?
Great food, phenomenal drinks and warm service in a smart, unique setting.
Food and service were excellent.

The quality and freshness of the food is impeccable. I’ve been here quite a few times already and I can definitely say they are consistent. Drinks are quite pricey but the scenery makes up for it. If your celebrating something special or just feel like treating yourself it’s money well spent.
Feels like a fire hazard
It was good...
Great food, excellent service
One of my favorite cocktail bars in the city. Excellent food too.
One of our favorite joints!!
Good place to grab a drink with a very knowledgable staff!
Great atmosphere. Steak and chicken were phenomenal.  Dessert was exquisite. Cocktails were outstanding. The bartender was a top notch professional. Highly recommend.
Excellent selection of whisky, great ambience and a warm welcome.
This place is easily one of my favorite fall/winter bars.
Best happy hour in Chicago’s river north!
Great food and atmosphere. All you can eat for $28. Wide variety of foods to chose from fresh and delicious.  It was allot of fun cooking your own food!
Awesome cocktails, delicious food and nice environment! One of the best places to be in Chicago
The butternut Squash soup was soooo good. Would definitely go back just for it
Been here a couple times and each time is just as good as the first. Highly recommend!

The Franklin Room is a charming restaurant with some really good burgers. The food was enjoyable though I did not feel as full as I hoped. Nonetheless, I did appreciate the level of courtesy from the staff, but noticeably, someone of my party received a completely wrong order; though, mine was made to my own expectations.
Open late but menu is pretty limited.

The drinks are a bit overpriced but the place has nice ambience and awesome bartender. I ordered my go-to Tom Collins and our bartender educated us on different types of gin and how it's changes the flavor of Tom Collins. Great place to go for a few bites and drinks with friends.
Nice scenery. Steak left something to be desired

Cozy, warm, inviting, secluded - Franklin has a speakeasy vibe but it's a proper whiskey restaurant and is quite well known. I am not a whiskey drinker but the abundance of choices were amazing. I had heard quite a bit about their small plates options and I liked it. The food is essentially bar food but elevated, easily and tastily filling and not overwhelming heavy even though some options are fried. The service is very friendly without trying too hard and I really liked our server. He was attentive, concerned with not just my table but others as well and genuinely a pleasant guy. I had a mojito even though it wasn't part of their drinks menu and our server was kind enough to get it made. My overall experience was wonderful and relaxing because of the ambience and service. I look forward to visiting again.
Great selection of scotch selection of scotch and knowledgeable staff.
Swanky and great lunch
Cheap lunch drinks. Great spicy bourbon burger and apps!

One of the best whisky selections in downtown Chicago! Bartenders who know their stuff, and you can talk whisky with them forever. Food is a bit pricey, but that comes with the area, and is not too much of a surprise.
Becoming one of my favorite places to dine at! Great food and their drink specials at lunch are killer! Highly recommend this spot!
My drinks were nice, a little on the pricey side tho.
For a whiskey joint, I was surprised our waiter didnt know what vermouth was... otherwise, a great spot
Awesome bar with good drink options. Isn't much room around the bar tho. Would recommend getting a table instead of standing at the bar. The wait staff was very helpful and nice. Will be back soon!
Incredible selection of whiskey
Try the rib-eye and the old fashion...both spectacular!
Oh man, if your haven't seen their lunch specials, go look. And the food is amazing
(Translated by Google) Relindo ... excellent cuisine ..!  (Original) Relindo... excelente la cocina..!
The environment was nice, the steak was good, the waiters were polite and attentive
Super deep drink menu.
Great food and a fun, eclectic cocktail menu with some serious drinks.

Hands down one of the best steaks I've ever had. Cooked to perfection and served at an astoundingly well stocked bar. Our bartender Grace was very knowledgeable and extremely helpful with suggestions from the massive whiskey list. Will be returning at my earliest possible opportunity.

Solid. We went on Sunday night ‘industry’ night and food was pretty good, was just a little slow on the service and he wasn’t super friendly. If I was in the area, I’d stop in for a drink but not sure I’d go out of my way in the future
Unremarkable meal, honestly was pretty mediocre. The Wisconsin cheese curds were good though.

(Translated by Google) Beautiful bar. Not strictly speaking a speakeasy but an excellent lounge. Oysters are not bad but ask without toping if you like them raw ... The bartender is excellent and knows his job and his cocktail card on the fingertips!  (Original) Superbe bar. Pas à proprement parlé un speakeasy mais un excellent lounge. Les huîtres sont pas mal mais demandez sans toping si vous les aimez crues... Le bartender est excellent et connaît son métier et sa carte de cocktail sur le bout des doigts!!
Food food, a Little bit noisy
Great place for a solid whiskey cocktail.  Had the George T. Stagg old fashioned.....bartender made it perfectly.

Large selections of whiskey and very friendly staff. The mussels were delicious!! They do have happy hour specials depending on the time and day you visit. I sat at the bar and ordered food. Went there about 5.30 on Saturday which wasn’t busy but by the time I left it was pretty crowded inside. Even when it's busy they do not skip you and always stay on top to refill your water or ask if you would like an another drink to make sure you are satisfied with the service.
Excelent selection of wisky and food knolagable staff
Good food, nice ambience.
Pretty expensive, but well worth the money.  The lamb shank was amazing and the service was perfection.  We had a group of 20 folks and they took care of us for a couple hours perfectly.

I will be here a lot more. All we had were a few drinks and some bar apps but everything we had was extremely delicious. Definitely worth checking out if you are a whiskey fan. Tons of options and the staff was very receptive and energized, not to mention knowledgeable. Get the rosemary nuts while you're at it. So good.
Amazing place. Beautiful decor & great service!
Good quality food and drinks, but a little on the pricey side.

A many faceted place. A meeting place for happy hour, a restaurant and a serious drinking establishment. Specialing in various whiskey the have a complete c selection for serious aficinados. My son is a bourbon specialist in Denver and he says it is a thorough list. Blow up picturs
Very good steakhouse I havent been to before. I would reccomend it. Its pricey but worth it.
Great food, good service at the bar, and no plastic!
Good food and drinks.

Big fan of the old fashioned style around here, and the old fashioned menu. Literally. One of the best old fashioneds in Chicago. Their happy hour is pretty dope as well and the whiskey boy is an absolutely wonderful substitution for your favorite whiskey cocktail for only $7. I love hitting this place up right after work or even later into the evening.
the food was excellent.  the draft beer selection was pretty good as well.
Great drink and food. Get ready to spend 💸
Good spot. Good food. Noisy but not bad.  A good vibe on Monday evening. Wine list limited but we had a Shiraz that was great.

We were here for our friend’s birthday dinner And I was very pleasantly surprised by how good the food was! I totally thought it was more of a bar. Everything we had was delicious, even the simple thing like Mac and Cheese or Pasta. The Cocktails were also good, plus the service was great. Food came out really fast though, so if you like to enjoy one thing at a time make sure to let them know.

Nice food and cocktails are served here but the price is quite high. the tiny crab cakes cost almost $20 and the oysters are exactly the size of my thumb. I expected bigger portion at their price point.
Three drink were great one of the best Old Fashions I've had.
Happy hour deals on oysters and a whiskey cocktail are pretty great. Excellent cocktail menu and good service. Can get crowded at times so I'd suggest reserving a table or showing up early.
Gosh dang best scallops you'll find this side of Appalachia
Awesome place for happy hour and even for dinner.
Nice quaint below the surface speak easy style!
Excellent cocktails. Good happy hour specials, including delicious $1.50 oysters and half-price Whiskey Boys on Tuesday.
Interesting cocktails well made. Delicious cheese curds and fantastic key lime pie. Fun, cozy, warm decor. Would go again.
Amazing food! I would recommend Steak Frites.

I went there for a dinner.  Actually, I went there to celebrate my anniversary. This place was on my "want to go" list, so this was a great opportunity to stop by. Atmosphere is awesome 5/5! I have no words to say about it! Nice, intimate,  silent music in the background...beautiful. Food was good, 4/5. I ordered prime steak salad and my partner had a lamb shank.  Prices are affordable. I attached some pics so you can see how it looks like. Overall 4.5 of 5.
Great lunch special for drinks

Would have rated less.  No ADA compliance had to stand with no effort to assist with a member of our group that was unable to stand.  Sat on steps.  Had to leave because no accommodations after several requests.
This is a really nice speakeasy with a great drink selection. The ambience is nice and intimate.
Beef sandwich, yum.
Beautiful spot with great atmosphere. Smoking deal on the restaurant week menu. The old fashioned was especially good.
You're partly paying for the location, but the wine but the glass selection is great, the food was good, and the service was top notch.
Everything was tasty, the food is so expensive for a lunch,  1/2 soup and sandwich for 16? Offset a bit by really really cheap draft beers. Totally worth it if you have a few beers at lunch.
One of the classier venues on the authentic Chicago speakeasy circuit. The food is phenomenal!
Very cute and chill atmosphere. Food and drinks were amazing.
Great selection of whiskey. Cocktails are right on. Food is just fine though. Would not recommend the oysters.

Excellent food and cocktails. Quality ingredients with careful attention to balancing complementary flavors. Highly recommend the French dip - this version features flavorful, perfectly braised short rib instead of traditional sliced roast beef.
Best first experience in Chicago and best whiskey experience ever
Nice experience, great food
Surf and Turf burger is the best I've ever had. Great selection of whiskey and bourbon.
Good food, good beer and good service.
Excellent onion soup
Best whisky choice I have seen for long
Drinks were tasty, lobster mac n cheese was so-so (lobster and pasta were over cooked 🙁), attentive service
The drink specials at lunch are redonk.  Had the mushroom grilled cheese and it. was. SO. good. :) Definitely would recommend making a reservation at lunch because it is always packed!
Amazing food and service. Had the Surf n Turf burger and couldn't have been more satisfied!
Very classy décor, great food, and a whiskey selection that will make your head spin. Highly recommended!
Great happy hour spot, with an excellent choice of whiskey
Excellent drinks and food. Service was awesome. Will become a favorite stop every time I'm in Chicago

Vegetarians beware, there is only one entree to choose from and it is a very average pasta. Otherwise the Franklin is cozy and quite happening, busy even on a Wednesday night, with good (but expensive!) drinks and service.
Fantastic workplace happy hour venue!
Wide selection of bourbon and scotch
Amazing food and atmosphere! I will come back.

Food was great.  Excellent drinks. Desserts a high point, particularly the apple crisp (deconstructed).  Pricey. Crowded.  We had a table reserved and had to wait 20 minutes when we arrived for our reserved table to open up.  Pet peeve.
The food and drinks are ok. The wide selections of spirits is quite good but had better food and drinks with the same amount we spent here.
Excellent selection of whiskey. Only had a couple small plates, but they were delicious. I will go back again.
Great mood and ambiance. Food was fantastic, service was great as well.
Nice place, great.drinks
Best soft shell crab sandwich!
Fun and tasty cocktail menu, excellent food, and a stylish atmosphere.
Cosy and cool place for Hangouts and relaxation
Nice atmosphere, good menu

Love the style and location.  The decor is very comfortable and perfectly lit.  Beautiful, well stocked bar and the bar service is good.  If you plan on going during a weekend, make reservations, the seating is limited.  The food was excellent.  I highly recommend anything meat off the menu.  Not many kitchens get medium rare right, this one mailed it.  The only knock is the table service.  This was fairly slow.  Drinks ordered from the table that had to be mixed too about 7-10 minutes to arrive.  If you have a drink you like order a couple or go to the bar to place it.
Great selection of whiskey, bartenders that know how to mix a drink.  Can buy by the quarter bottle.  Great staff
Great food, good ambience, better drinks, nice tasting food albeit smaller portions
Great vibe even on a weeknight, tasty appetizer menu, awesome service. Will definitely come back
Service was good. Food was good. It was a bit quiet when we went during lunch on a Tuesday.
Nice place
The food was delicious and unique, the service was excellent.  April anticipated all our needs and exceeded expectations.p
The food was excellent, the service was attentive, charming, and knowledgeable. The short ribs were mouth-wateringly flavorful and so, so tender. Went on an of town date night and was very pleased.
I came here for dinner and had an amazing time. The place is beautiful and the food and drinks are great + the service was impeccable, will definitely come back.
Legit happy hour with oyster and cocktails. Never tried anything else other than happy hour . But pretty solid HH selection .
Great atmosphere. Went for lunch and the food was very good. Great place for a business lunch. Fast and friendly service.
Nice bar
Good food.
Excellent service, food was amazing. Drinks are well worth it
Awesome drinks!! Beautiful food.  Lovely atmosphere!  Great staff....  Surprisingly generous pours, and good prices.
It’s great place to go and you don’t know where to go in the River North area. They also have excellent lunch specials and wine specials.
One the great hidden gems of Chicago . Peter is the man.  Highly recommend for any occasion at any time.
Incredible scotch selection with knowledgeable bartenders. Class act.
Fantastic establishment.
Best Manhattan and old fashioned I've had. Worth the price for a drink or two in the evening. I also recommend them for lunch. Went here for lunch and got a salad and $1 wine! Yum!
Cocktails here are fantastic. One of the best Old Fashioneds I've ever had, and certainly the most expensive. Bartenders are friendly pros. Low light, wooden atmosphere inside - very nice.

Great place!  Came here for a birthday dinner and it was pretty crowded, but we were able to find a couple spots at the bar while we waited for our table to become available.  We had a reservation, but the party before us decided to sit and chat for an extended time, so it delayed things.  The staff at Franklin Room was very apologetic for the wait, even though it was out of their control.  They even brought us a complimentary appetizer, which was extremely generous.  The food was awesome!  We had the Squid Ink Pasta and the Surf & Turf Burger.  I would highly recommend both dishes, as well as the Cauliflower Parmesan Tots.  That probably would not have been my first choice for an appetizer, but after trying it, I don’t think I would ever skip it when we go back.  The entire staff was extremely friendly and our server (I believe her name was Alla) was very attentive, despite how busy they were.  The atmosphere is really cool and the prices were not crazy, given it’s River North.  Glad we discovered this place on Open Table and we’ll definitely be back!
Excellent service and pulled pork.

The waitress I had was incredibly attentive and detail oriented. I shared a burger, oysters, and shrimp with my boyfriend. It was all so delicious and the portion sizes were perfect. The oysters were top notch and are served with sauces that are out of this world. The atmosphere is classy and upscale, but no black tie necessary. I will return!
Good food. A bit expensive for what you get
It's fine
Awesome bar with a great cocktail selection. Their Friday lunch special is the best in the area; be sure to get reservations if you're going to try it on a Friday - they get busy!

This restaurant in downtown Chicago Is Awesome The Venue itself is very graded as a nice dark atmosphere with a berry mobster style feel to the back corners of it which I really like. The food was very good my dad got a burger there that had a soft shell crab and an egg on it and it is the best burger that I have ever tried and he said that it's the best burger he has ever had. Me and my family were there to celebrate my cousin and her boyfriend's law school graduation and I couldn't have imagined a better place. I will definitely be coming back when I'm in the area. Service is really great and the waiter was quick and came when we need a drinks or more food and offered us appetizers and made recommendations on what we're good and what were not, overall a really awesome place!
Bartenders are amazing here.  Don't need shy to  order off the menu.

Good place. A little pricey for what you get, and service was slow and off. For example, they did not bring us sugar for our espresso and we had to hunt the server down. But overall a good experience.  The popovers are quite good to start with, along with the burrata. The halibut was good!
Neat atmosphere, good cocktail list.
Wait staff was so nice. Really enjoyed my Whiskey Boy and the oysters. The salmon was delicious!
Pricey but worth it. Great night cap and surprisingly well put together menu. Cant miss the Mon-Fri $1 beers for lunch.
Great atmosphere and food.
The Franklin Room offers.one of the largest selection of Burbons, Wiskeys and Scotch's in Chicago. A well balanced menu with many appetizers is.sure to please.

Had reservations but we all know how that goes. Although it didn't take long to get our table. The waitress was very attentive and the drinks are to die for. I had the long train ride to R something and if you've ever had cucumbers for a street vendor with chili then this is your drink! Also you must try the truffle fries! They are outta this world.
Really cool speakeasy-type lounge, but the cocktails are super overpriced.
Great happy hour. Get the rock shrimp!
Great atmosphere, really great food. Order the cheese curds and fries. I loved my steak frites.
Get the lunch special.
Great drinks
Great drinks and the food is also well done.

I had the spicy bourbon burger and it was very tasty. I wasn’t sure how I would feel about the Kim chi on it but it was delicious. The fries are also great. Had one of the whiskey boys on happy hour as well as the oysters. Whiskey boy is nice and smooth and the oysters tasted very fresh. Waiter was very attentive and friendly.
Swank place to grab a cocktail as well as a good place for dinner
Great lunch specials. Dollar beers. Cool atmosphere
$1 lunch drinks? Awesome food? I'm in.
Don't go here.
Came for drinks at lunch with coworkers.. Took 1 hour to get 1 drink and when we got our bill everything was wrong. Took another 10 minutes to get our bill and cards back. Horrible horrible service.

Great place. Very nice selection of bourbon. The staff is always super friendly. The food is pretty good. The food is a little expensive but if you go there during lunch you can get $1 beers or $3 mixed drinks which makes the whole lunch a pretty reasonable price. Unless you want to sit at the bar with just 2 people, you should make reservations during lunch.

Great cocktails - great service - seating is a little tight and tables a little too close which prevents from having a thoughtful conversation without introducing a bit of a shouting match. Would def it will still go back for the cocktails, food and service.
Great atmosphere, cocktails we're solid, great service!
The lunch specials are ludicrously good. If you ever need $3 martinis at lunchtime, this is your spot. Also, I think they have every whiskey ever made? Oh, and the food is miraculous.
Good food, very good service. Decent beer selection (all cans/blts, nothing on tap), great selection of whiskey/bourbon
Great selection of drinks, friendly staff. Food is good, but I wouldn't say it's great, the apps are my go-to here.
Great service and food was delish!
Great happy hour. Great cocktails and whiskey selection
Cool spot with tasty but slightly over-priced cocktails. Really solid happy hour deals though. I’d go back!
Excelent place great food and variety of whiskeys, loved the surf N turf burger
Good food.
Dont order the drink that has something on fire. All other are good!

A must place if you are whiskey lover ot may be not because I frankly do not like that much (vodka person). But after coming here and trying out the cocktails hete, it was amazing. Do try their specials. All of them are good. Oh, the whiskey boy comes in a flask which is yours to take.
Great place.  Amazing ambiance.  The perfect place if you live whiskey
This place is amazing! Great food, great staff and great prices (especially during happy hour)
Cauliflower tots are awesome
Great bar selection, absolutely stocked to the gills with pretty much anything you can think of. The hurger was delicious as well and the lunch menu has $1 drinks. Great atmosphere.
Great food and Top notch wiskey
Beautifully decorated and great setting for private or social gatherings.
Good food, great drinks!
They have a great happy hour!
Neighborhood gem!
Great experience
We got there close to closing time and they were very welcoming and we were able to get at least two drinks. Definitely will be back
You were drunk while writing this review... But trust me just go back...
I loved the atmosphere but the food was only 4 stars in my opinion.

We so enjoyed our dining experience!  it began with receiving a call a few days before our reservation too confirm and to check for special dietary request.  We were seated immediately upon arrival. we had 8 people in our party. Dan our server was excellent! request him. he was attentive and knowledgeable! the Signature Whiskey Boy was firyah! dear to our hearts because it made with Kentucky Bourbon! The salmon was seared with this incredible crisp that makes your mouth water! the Mushroom risotto was layered and delicious! the key lime pie and the apple crisp was fresh and a perfect end to a wonderful meal! we will definitely come back!
Great staff, lovely atmosphere, and great bourbon selection
The food hear was good, but the main thing I'd come back for we're the drinks. They we're by far the cocktails I've ever had.

I loved everything! The service was great...we sat at the bar. Atmosphere was nice for a date but would also be wonderful for a group for dinner, but also somewhere to meet for cocktails/apps after work or before a night out. The truffle fries...omg! Surf and turf burger was maybe one of the best burgers I’ve ever had. Crunch shrimp is on point. The key lime pie was light and fluffy and such a treat. Long train to Fresno, Blood and Sand, and The Pisco Sour were wonderful. GREAT cocktials. Perfectly balanced without being overly boozy or complex no matter what liquor you prefer. HIGHLY recommend. Did not disappoint!
This was our first time here and we will definitely be back! Everything about it experience was great! The food, the service, the ambiance, everything. Highly recommend The Franklin Room!
Great whiskey. Good atmosphere.
Excellent food and cocktails. Great ambience. Try the short ribs!
Some of the best food I've ever had.
Foood was incredible!

You can get great drinks everywhere in Chicago. This place is special. They are one of the places that know what and can tell you a lot about what they have prepared. I just tell them what I'm thinking and they make it happen. Totally open my eyes to a huge list of great bottles.
Great space for a date and my husband enjoyed the whiskey tasting flights. Good food and the servers were casual and attentive.
Our server Dan was fantastic. I highly recommend the salmon! The stronger drinks were good, but not great.
Great whiskey selection
Cool place. Great atmosphere. Good food. Good service. We’ll be back for sure.
Great atmosphere and dining experience

I love this place! I kept walking past it and my friend and I decided to try the Franklin Room. Fantastic atmosphere, you walk down a short flight of steps into a cozy but active little world which allows you hear your dining partner. Wonderful music, the classics, Sinatra etc. Food was fabulous. We had black risotto with mushrooms, delicious mussels with a miso/bourbon broth and we each had a salad, one beet and one nicoise. Every course was delicious and cooked perfectly! The service was also excellent. I almost didn't want to write this review and keep this little gem to myself! Will absolutely be returning, a perfect spot for the winter! Oh and they have a fantastic bar with BACKS to the bar stools although we sat at a table, but it looked really nice! Love it!

This is, without doubt, the best restaurant I have ever been to in Chicago (a few business trips through the past few years).  I came on a Tuesday night, and the service was sincerely some of the best I have ever had. Their $1 oyster and $5 whiskey boy happy hour is unreal on its face, and the taste of both are completely out of hand too. The oysters are completely done up, and the whiskey boy was basically the best old fashion I've had in my life. And the lamb shank was fantastic.  All in all, if you live in Chicago, or just passing through like me, you owe it to yourself to check this place out. You will not be disappointed.
